<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN XIII. Agni.</h3>  
<p>1. BRING song and hymn to Agni, Asura-slayer, enlightener of all and thought-bestower.<br> Like an oblation on the grass, to please him, I bring this to Vai&#347;v&#257;nara, hymn-inspirer.<br> 2 Thou with thy flame, O Agni, brightly glowing, hast at thy birth filled full the earth and heaven.<br> TIOU with thy might, Vai&#347;v&#257;nara J&#257;tavedas, settest the Gods free frodi the curse that bound them.<br> 3 Agni, when, born thou lookedst on all creatures, like a brisk herdsman moving round his cattle.<br> The path to prayer, Vai&#347;v&#257;nara, thou foundest. Ye Gods, preserve us evermore with blessings.</p>  
